Please translate each line literally into English.
82 La miserella intra tutti costoro 83 pareva dir: «Segnor, fammi vendetta 84 di mio figliuol ch’è morto, ond’ io m’accoro»;
85 ed elli a lei rispondere: «Or aspetta 86 tanto ch’i’ torni»; e quella: «Segnor mio», 87 come persona in cui dolor s’affretta,
88 «se tu non torni?»; ed ei: «Chi fia dov’ io, 89 la ti farà»; ed ella: «L’altrui bene 90 a te che fia, se ’l tuo metti in oblio?»;
91 ond’ elli: «Or ti conforta; ch’ei convene 92 ch’i’ solva il mio dovere anzi ch’i’ mova: 93 giustizia vuole e pietà mi ritene».

query.result:
82 The little miserable woman among all these 83 seemed to say: “Lord, avenge me 84 of my son who is dead, for which I grieve”;
85 and he to her responded: “Now wait 86 until I return”; and she: “My Lord”, 87 as a person in whom sorrow hastens,
88 “if you do not return?”; and he: “Who will be where I am, 89 will make it for you”; and she: “The good of others 90 to you what will it be, if you put your own into oblivion?”;
91 whereupon he: “Now comfort yourself; for it is necessary 92 that I fulfill my duty before I move: 93 justice wants and piety retains me”.
